metadata.name: Moon Rising
metadata.description:
I'd visualised this shot after visiting this location in Mangawhai (two hours north of Auckland) a few years ago, but had to wait for the full moon to rise at the same time as the sunset to ensure the pink tones and making sure there was a good chance of clear skies.

I would say it was worth the wait.


12 inch x 12 inch print on Hahnemuhle Rag Fine Print included
